<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17640502-41">
               <interp inst="t17640502-41" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640502-41" type="year" value="1764"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640502-41" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17640502"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640502-41" type="date" value="17640502"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17640502-41-off228-c269" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-41-defend345 t17640502-41-off228 t17640502-41-verdict232"></join>
         
               <p>268. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17640502-41-defend345" type="defendantName">
                     Joseph 
                     Belfore 
                  <interp inst="t17640502-41-defend345" type="surname" value="Belfore"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-41-defend345" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-41-defend345" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for the <rs id="t17640502-41-off228" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640502-41-off228" type="offenceCategory" value="kill"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-41-off228" type="offenceSubcategory" value="murder"></interp>
               wilful murder of 
                     
                        <persName id="t17640502-41-victim347" type="victimName">
                           John 
                           Delahay 
                        <interp inst="t17640502-41-victim347" type="surname" value="Delahay"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17640502-41-victim347" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17640502-41-victim347" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-41-off228 t17640502-41-victim347"></join>
                     </persName>
                      
                  , by driving two horses drawing a cart, over his back, by which means he instantly died
            </rs>, <rs id="t17640502-41-cd229" type="crimeDate">April 23</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-41-off228 t17640502-41-cd229"></join>. *</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17640502-41-person348">
                  Edward 
                  Nixon 
               <interp inst="t17640502-41-person348" type="surname" value="Nixon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-41-person348" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-41-person348" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On Easter-Monday I saw the prisoner driving two horses, drawing a cart; they were stopped by the wheel going into a hole; the prisoner whipped them sadly: the children got out of the cart.</p>
               <p>Q. Where was this?</p>
               <p>Nixon. This was in <placeName id="t17640502-41-crimeloc230">Church-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17640502-41-crimeloc230" type="placeName" value="Church-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17640502-41-crimeloc230" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-41-off228 t17640502-41-crimeloc230"></join>. When the children got in again, and they were going on, the deceased cry'd, O dear, I shall be down! the prisoner kept driving on, and the <rs id="t17640502-41-viclabel231" type="occupation">child</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-41-victim347 t17640502-41-viclabel231"></join> fell from the shafts, and the wheel went over its back.</p>
               <p>Q. How old was the child?</p>
               <p>Nixon. It was 7 years and 7 months old; the prisoner shoved the child up two or three times with his hand before it fell; that kept crying out, O dear, I shall be down, I shall be down! the prisoner strove to break the fall.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17640502-41-person349">
                  William 
                  Ambross 
               <interp inst="t17640502-41-person349" type="surname" value="Ambross"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-41-person349" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-41-person349" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner with his cart full of children; the cart stopped: there came some gentlemen by, and whipped the horses; the children got out, and after that they got in again; there were two more upon the shafts: one of the boys cry'd out, O dear, I shall be down! the prisoner lifted him up, and in a little way going, the child fell under the near wheel, and the wheel ran over his back, and killed the child.</p>
               <p>Q. Did the prisoner do all in his power to save him?</p>
               <p>Ambross. For all I know, he did.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17640502-41-verdict232" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640502-41-verdict232" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               Acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
